Reasoning: The paper discusses the complexity of functions computed by small Turing machines, which falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The study of Turing machines also involves the analysis of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), as well as the logical foundations of computer science (cs.LO). The paper also touches on information theory (cs.IT) in its discussion of the representation of functions, and programming languages (cs.PL) in its description of the Turing machine model.
